The New York Police Department confirmed the death of fashion designer Kate Spade, 55, on Tuesday. It was reported under her birth name, Katherine Noel Brosnahan. What is known about her death: Tributes: After learning of Spade's death, fashion writer Abby Gardner tweeted, "Ask any girl around my age about getting her first boxy Kate Spade bag and she’ll probably have a story to tell you. It was a magnificently simple cultural marker." Many other people tweeted about mental health issues, including television presenter Trenni Kusnierek, who said: "By all accounts, Kate Spade "had it all" — money, success, fame. None of these things matter when you are sick. Kate was not selfish. Kate was not weak. Kate was sick." Who was Kate Spade? Spade was a co-founder of the designer label Kate Spade New York, which she later sold. She most recently launched a new accessories label, Frances Valentine. The 55-year-old began her working life as accessoiries editor at the now-closed Mademoiselle magazine. In 1993 Spade launched her fashion label, Kate Spade New York, with her husband Andy.  Each evening at 1830 UTC, DW's editors send out a selection of the day's hard news and quality feature journalism. You can sign up to receive it directly here. kw/kms (AP, AFP, dpa, Reuters)